Stage 1 - Setup + UI-Focus

5/11/2025
    Mirrored the GitLab repo onto my GitHub repo to get the CI/CD configuration working 
    (GitLab did not have the permissions needed)

    Deployed the app via React + Vite.

    Coding out the skeleton for the app as a base.

    Added sql.js to run the SQL queries in the browser itself. 

21/12/2025
    Added the About modal to explain how the app works.

25/12/2025
    Added the Help modal to describe how to use the app.

    Enabling the Run button but not the full function yet.

26/12/2025
    The Run button prototype supports interactive query analysis, dynamically generating logical execution steps and visual plans in response to user input.

    Planning to make small upgrades to Run to highlight steps and nodes more informatively.

28/12/2025
    Added to Run step-through highlights for both steps and diagram visuals.

    Cleaned up the code by separating the different parts of the code in separate files and folders.

    Pushing all the initial spine for the code into the github. 

6/1/2026
    Added the general step details in each step-through.

    Added the example queries feature where a range of example queries are present to quickly test or present a demonstration.

13/1/2026
    Added the format button to clean up queries that the user would input.

    Optimized the clear button to do more.

    Did some slight fixing on tiny bugs just to ensure thoroughness for app features.

Phase 2 - Advancement

15/1/2026
    Began coding the advanced step details and diagram.

    Added the setup SQL button for users to provide their own table names for their own understanding or classes.

4/2/2026
    Implemented GitLab CI pipeline with a Docker-based runner to automatically build and validate the application.

8/2/2026
    Implemented persistent Setup SQL saving using browser localStorage, allowing users to store and reuse multiple custom database schemas across sessions.

    Added functionality to apply, delete, and manage saved table setups, enabling iterative practice without retyping schema definitions.

    Introduced a Reset Database feature to restore the default demo schema and resolve setup conflicts.

    Improved setup feedback messaging to distinguish between successful application, repeated application, and setup errors.

    Fixed an issue where saved setups were unintentionally overwritten on page refresh by correcting localStorage state initialisation logic.

11/2/2026
    Refactored the overall UI layout in response to supervisor feedback regarding visual clutter and overcrowding on the left panel.

    Transitioned to a code-editor inspired layout (similar to Code-Pad), separating concerns clearly:
    - Left panel dedicated purely to the SQL editor.
    - Right panel reorganised into tab-based outputs (Results, Steps, Diagram, Schema).
    - Top bar centralised primary actions (Dialect selector, Run, Share).

    Removed duplicate Run button from the editor panel to reduce visual noise and establish a single primary execution action in the TopBar.

    Restricted step navigation controls (Back, Next, Reset) to appear only when the "Steps" tab is active, improving contextual clarity.

    Moved Setup SQL functionality into a dedicated "Schema" tab to declutter the editor and better separate database setup from query execution.

    Removed the Example Queries dropdown in favour of dialect-based starter queries.

    Implemented automatic starter query loading for the default SQLite dialect on initial page load, providing immediate usability without manual input.

    Added dialect-switch behaviour:
        - Automatically loads starter query if the editor is empty.
        - Prompts user before overwriting existing queries when switching dialects.

    Improved overall UI consistency and reduced cognitive load, aligning the application more closely with a professional editor workflow.

12/2/2026
    Continued UI simplification following the structural refactor.

    Removed the Example Queries feature to streamline the editor interface and reduce redundant controls.

    Implemented automatic starter query loading for the default SQLite dialect on initial application load, ensuring immediate usability.

    Refined dialect switching behaviour:
        - Starter query loads automatically if the editor is empty.
        - Confirmation modal appears before overwriting existing user input when changing dialects.

    Verified Schema tab functionality through manual testing:
        - Confirmed table creation via Setup SQL.
        - Confirmed data insertion and querying of user-defined tables.
        - Validated saved setup persistence via localStorage.
        - Tested database reset behaviour.

